    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">857.014/–</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Norwegian Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Arentz</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to acknowledge the receipt of your note of
                    February 9th in which you inform me of the occupation of the island of Jan
                    Mayen, in the Arctic Ocean, by Christoffer Evensen Ruud, a Norwegian citizen,
                    during an expedition in August, 1917, for the purpose of prospecting for ore and
                    minerals, to establish a station for catch of animals, and to start seal oil
                    manufacturing and ore washing. I have taken pleasure in communicating this
                    information to the appropriate branch of this Government.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
